pdc@dcs.ed.ac.uk (Paul Crowley) writes:
: Can any cypher be used to generate a secure random number generator by
: encrypting the output of a normal RNG?  Or does the very high redundancy
: of the normal RNG provide too strong a lever against the cypher?

With a good cypher you don't need the RNG.  A simple counter will suffice
as input and the cipher will output a crypto strong RNG.  Granted it is
subject to known-plaintext attack but any good cypher has to withstand
this anyway.

: 
: I ask because the idea of encyphering my text before I write it appeals
: to me...

Me too.  Let me know if you figure out how. :-)

Bob
